description: Many Alberta teachers say the latest contract offer from their employers and union isn’t good enough to stop them from striking.
title: Why some Alberta teachers will vote against the latest contract offer

description: Six-year-old Darius Macdougall went missing Sunday morning while on a walk with family members at a campground near Blairmore, Alta.
title: More crews arriving as search for missing Alberta boy approaches one-week mark

description: Alberta Premier Danielle Smith's government says it is planning to introduce legislation that would allow it to ignore international agreements signed by Ottawa.
title: Alberta considers new law allowing it to ignore international agreements signed by Canada

description: Prime Minister Mark Carney's government is picking up where the Trudeau administration left off and will make an attempt to reform the military justice system. Legislation to take the investigation and prosecution of sexual offenses away from military police was lost when Parliament was prorogued. It's now back.
title: Ottawa tries — again — to strip military of power to investigate sexual offences

description: The Dutch government has agreed to return thousands of fossils to Indonesia from a world-renowned collection, after a commission ruled they were removed in the colonial era "against the will of the people," the education ministry announced on Friday.
title: The Netherlands returns 'Java Man,' thousands of colonial-era fossils taken from Indonesia

description: The former high school football player who killed four people inside a Manhattan office tower that houses the headquarters of the NFL, was suffering from the degenerative brain disease CTE, New York's medical examiner said Friday.
title: Gunman who blamed NFL for hiding brain injury dangers had CTE: medical examiner

description: Sinclair is one of two major broadcast owners that had not agreed to resume airing Jimmy Kimmel Live! this week after Disney lifted a nearly week-long suspension of the show.
title: Kimmel show to return to ABC's Sinclair stations on Friday

description: Jimmy Kimmel Live! will be back on ABC-affiliated stations of both Sinclair Broadcasting and Nexstar Media Group starting tonight, the companies said Friday.
title: Sinclair, Nexstar to air Jimmy Kimmel Live! again starting tonight

description: A wildfire near Peachland, B.C., that has forced the evacuation of hundreds of properties in the Okanagan municipality has tripled in reported size.
title: Evacuation orders, alerts remain in place as wildfire near Peachland, B.C., triples in size

description: Health Canada has issued a recall notice for 104,195 toaster ovens in Canada due to a burn hazard.
title: Health Canada recalls over 104,000 Oster toaster ovens due to burn risk

description: The Canadian Food Inspection Agency says the "ongoing delay" in carrying out the cull of ostriches at a British Columbia farm presents "potential animal and human health risks."
title: Stay of ostrich cull in southeast B.C. an ongoing potential health risk, CFIA says
Canada's cyber agency warns of 'serious and urgent' attack on tech used by remote workers
Need a Canada vs. England Women's Rugby World Cup bandwagon guide? We'll try

description: In an Edmonton hotel ballroom, representatives from the nuclear industry are buzzing about the potential to power Alberta by splitting atoms. The province has been excited about nuclear before, and while the demand for it is growing globally, there are still big challenges to getting an industry off the ground.
title: Alberta has flirted with nuclear power before. Is it now ready to make a move?

description: Canada's monthly gross domestic product rebounded from three months of contraction to grow by 0.2 per cent in July, as mining, manufacturing and wholesale trade boosted growth.
title: Canada's GDP rebounds in July after contracting for 3 months

description: Facing international isolation, accusations of war crimes and growing pressure to end a conflict he has continued to escalate, dozens of delegates from multiple nations walked out of the United Nations hall as Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu went up to speak.
title: As Netanyahu addresses UN, dozens of delegates walk out in protest

description: A member of Irish rap group Kneecap was charged too late with a terrorism offence for allegedly displaying a flag of Iran-backed Lebanese militia Hezbollah, a London court ruled on Friday, throwing out his prosecution.
title: Kneecap member's terrorism case in U.K. 'null and void,' judge rules

description: Two experts say more companies will move production to other countries in order to have a stable business relationship rather than dealing with tariff uncertainty.
title: As combine manufacturer shifts production to Europe from U.S., experts say tariffs mean more may follow

description: One Saskatchewan man has taken his love for fruitcake to a new level, and gained a social media following of more than 37,000 people in the process.
title: Who says everyone hates fruitcake? Sask. man started on 700 Christmas fruitcake orders this summer

description: A London homeowner says her insurance company has been little help nearly five months after a destructive storm caused her backyard tree to fall onto her house, putting a hole in the roof.
title: A tree fell on her house in April, but she's still waiting for repairs due to insurance delays

description: After two weeks of heavy foot traffic, Shuh Orchards in West Montrose, Ont., reports as many as 500 pounds of apples have been stolen, prompting the farm to ban wagons, strollers and backpacks. Agritourism Ontario says many farms are having a similar issue with theft.
title: Ontario orchard bans strollers, wagons and backpacks after some 500 pounds of apples stolen

description: Online true crime shows mark an evolution in how people engage with crime and mysteries — it's never been more interactive. And they create opportunities for those directly involved in cases to speak their minds, for better or for worse.
title: With few answers and rumours abounding, family of missing N.S. children take to YouTube

description: An exclusive CBC data analysis has found that since 2018, Ontario has spent over $200 million sending patients to U.S. clinics for procedures unavailable in Canada. The biggest expenditure under the program last year was a specialized cancer treatment called proton beam therapy — a treatment available in every G7 country except Canada.
title: Why Canadian taxpayers spend millions on U.S. medical treatments

description: Dr. Nada Al-Rub is spending a month in working in hospitals around Gaza. She says Al-Shifa has little to no equipment and that she and her colleagues have had to make due with limited resources and very complex injuries.
title: This doctor takes us through a day at Al-Shifa hospital in Gaza City

description: CBC News has learned Transport Canada was already aware of three prior incidents affecting the LionC school bus model — all involving fires or significant smoke — yet did not launch a formal defect investigation until another bus caught fire in Montreal earlier this month.
title: 2 Lion school buses caught fire. It took a 3rd for Transport Canada to launch investigation

description: DeAndre Anderson, 25, was arrested and charged in April 2024 with two counts of uttering threats “in support of the incel ideology,” say RCMP. The charges, following a joint investigation with Halton regional police and the FBI, are alleged to constitute terrorist activity under the code, police say.
title: Burlington, Ont., man tells court he's 'remorseful' for violent threats against women on incel website

description: More than three years after fleeing a war zone and planting roots in Canada, some Ukrainians say their future remains uncertain after the federal government's temporary residency program came to an end earlier this year.
title: More than 3 years after relocating to Canada, Ukrainians say their lives remain in limbo

description: The rationale for U.S. President Donald Trump's whiplash on Ukraine is being hotly debated in Europe and at NATO, where political leaders and experts are asking whether it's personal self-interest or an economical military strategy.
title: Trump's Ukraine pivot: Backing away, or backing a winner?

description: Single-use plastic items are a substantial contributor to litter across Canada, but compostable alternatives can follow a similar path. Marketplace set out to determine how items would break down if they ended up in our environment.
title: Which reusable grocery bags passed, and failed, Marketplace's durability test?

description: An Edmonton intensive-care physician who became well known in Alberta for his insights into the challenges facing the health-care system during the COVID-19 pandemic, died in a cycling accident on Sunday.
title: Colleagues, politicians pay tribute to prominent Edmonton doctor killed in mountain biking accident
